to the editor re in sketchy data trying to gauge iraq threat front page july 20 in addition to garnering public support for the invasion of iraq administration reports of iraqi bioweapons capability influenced many health care workers to step forward to be vaccinated against smallpox despite the known risks of the vaccine the 91 suspected probable and confirmed casualties of this effort should be counted among the mounting casualties of this war kathleen delaney md dallas july 20 2003

